This paper deals with neural networks and their learning mechanisms, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The paper also discusses synaptic plasticity, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on pattern recognition and memory consolidation also suggests it could be categorized under cs.SI (signal processing) or cs.SY (systems and control).
